hink about what will kill off the other bidder in august  schwarzman compared the obama administrations plan to raise carried interest taxes to hitlers invasion of poland in  a comment for which schwarzman later apologized in september  schwarzman was listed as a member of the international advisory board of the russian direct investment fund among blackstones largest investments were seaworld parks in  seaworld parks were the focus of the  film blackfish a documentary on killer whale attacks at these parks and the ethics of keeping them captive when asked about the film schwarzman said on record that seaworld trainer dawn brancheau should be blamed for her own death claiming that the veteran animal trainer broke multiple safety rules before she was pulled into a tank and killed by a sixton orca in february  blackstone said in a written statement that schwarzman misspoke in response to the question about blackfish the firm said its chief executive had not anticipated a question about the film and had not been briefed on the subject the firm said schwarzman does not plan to go back on cnbc to correct the record on air seaworld for its part said unequivocally that brancheau bore no blame dawn was one of the worlds most skilled and experienced marine mammal trainers her dedication to safety was among the many reasons she was so respected by her colleagues at seaworld and within the worldwide animal training community the company said in a written statement we have never said and do not believe that she was at fault for the events of february   personal lifeedit schwarzman met his first wife ellen philips during his second year at harvard business school where she worked as a researcher and helped grade essays she was the daughter of jesse philips a wealthy ohio industrialist they were married in  and divorced in  they had two children elizabeth born  married in november  to andrew curtis right edward frank also known as teddy born  married in november  to ellen marie zajac in  schwarzman married christine hearst an intellectualproperty lawyer who grew up on long island she was the daughter of peggie and peter mularchuk of hicksville new york her father was a fireman she was recently divorced from austin hearst grandson of newspaper tycoon randolph hearst rabbi bertram siegel coofficiated along with the rev sam matarazzo a roman catholic priest she has one child from a previous marriage he lives in a duplex apartment at  park avenue previously owned by the mayflower descendent george brewster and by john d rockefeller jr schwarzman purchased the apartment from saul steinberg in  for just under  million however an article in the new yorker claims that the apartment was purchased for  million on february   schwarzman celebrated his th birthday at the armory on park avenue guests included colin powell mayor of new york city michael bloomberg donald trump and cardinal edward m egan of new york the climax of the evening was a halfhour live performance by rod stewart for which he was reportedly paid  million in february  he had lavish th birthday party in florida estimated to have cost – million political and economic viewsedit schwarzman is a republican he is a longtime friend of president donald trump and provides outside counsel and currently chairs president donald trumps strategic and policy forum in response to criticism for his involvement with the trump administration schwarzman penned a letter to current schwarzman scholars arguing that having influence and providing sound advice is a good thing even if it attracts criticism or requires some sacrifice in early  he said that in a twocandidate race he would prefer donald trump to ted cruz saying that the nation needed a cohesive healing presidency not one thats lurching either to the right or to the left he had previously made a donation to marco rubio in  he also endorsed and fundraised for mitt romney in  in  schwarzman drew controversy for comparing president obamas proposal to increase taxation on carried interest profits to hitlers invasion of poland in  schwarzman later apologized for the analogy he raised  for george w bush wealth and philanthropyedit according to forbes magazine he has a net worth of  billion usd as of january  in  schwarzman was named as one of bloombergs  most influential people of the year in  schwarzman was again named as one of bloombergs  most influential people of the year in  schwarzman donated a new football stadium to abington senior high school—the stephen a schwarzman stadium in  schwarzman was listed among time magazines  most influential people in the world on march   schwarzman announced that he contributed  million toward the expansion of the new york public library for which he serves as a trustee the central reference building on nd street and fifth avenue was renamed the stephen a schwarzman building on may   peter salovey the president of yale university announced that schwarzman contributed  million to fund a campus center in the universitys historic commons dining facility additionally schwarzman is also a member of the berggruen institutes st century council schwarzman scholarsedit main article schwarzman scholars on april   schwarzman announced a  million personal gift to establish and endow a scholarship program in china schwarzman scholars modeled after the rhodes scholarship program schwarzman simultaneously announced a fundraising campaign with a goal of  million the schwarzman scholars program will be housed at tsinghua university one of chinas most prestigious universities the first class of  students is slated for  upon completion of schwarzman college designed by robert a m stern dean of the yale school of architecture in january  schwarzman was on the cover of the shanghai business review to share his vision about the chinese economy against the backdrop of his scholarship the story was supported by kevin rudd former prime minister of australia and on the international advisory board of schwarzman scholars president trumps strategic and policy forumedit main article strategic and policy forum in late  schwarzman helped put together a team of corporate executives to advise president donald trump on jobs and the economy the group includes jpmorgan chase jpm ceo jamie dimon walt disney dis boss bob iger and former ge leader jack welch in february schwarzman was named as chair of the member presidents strategic and policy forum which brings together ceos of americas biggest corporations banks and investment firms to consult with the president on how to create jobs and improve growth for the us economy infrastructure funds blackstone and saudi arabiaedit increasingly large investors such as blackstone are investing in infrastructure such as airports public works and railways blackstone with  billion in assets is expanding into infrastructure investments the blackstone group joined forces with saudi arabia in may  establishing a  billion infrastructure fund to invest in stateside infrastructure projects saudi arabia will provide  of the fund which could lead to  billion in total infrastructure investments on a leveraged basis referencesedit  stephen schwarzman blackstones  billion man forbes retrieved november     stephen schwarzman forbescom retrieved december     a b c nocera joe february   steve schwarzman explains why he counsels trump retrieved march   – via wwwbloombergcom   live from new york it’s steve schwarzman the new york times retrieved december     the worlds  richest jews   jewish world  jerusalem post jpostcom retrieved december     a b weddings  christine hearst s a schwarzman nytimescom november   retrieved december     past award recipients abingtonkpaus june   retrieved december     evan thomas and daniel gross taxing the super rich newsweek july    andrew clark the guardian profile stephen schwarzman the guardian june    the  most successful harvard business school graduates business insider retrieved november     david carey joh